|dead-url=no
}}</ref>。

==背景==
19世纪中期中国人开始移民到美国西部作矿工与[[第一条横贯大陆铁路|铁路]]等[[苦力|苦力]]工作
<ref>{{cite news
|last=Sayej
|first=Nadja
|url=https://www.theguardian.com/artanddesign/2019/jul/18/forgotten-by-society-how-chinese-migrants-built-the-transcontinental-railroad
|title='Forgotten by society' – how Chinese migrants built the transcontinental railroad
|date=Jul 18, 2019
|newspaper=The Guardian
|accessdate=2021-03-18
|archive-date=2021-05-11
|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210511161207/https://www.theguardian.com/artanddesign/2019/jul/18/forgotten-by-society-how-chinese-migrants-built-the-transcontinental-railroad
|dead-url=no
}}</ref>
<ref>{{cite web
|url=https://www.history.com/news/transcontinental-railroad-chinese-immigrants
|title=Building the Transcontinental Railroad: How 20,000 Chinese Immigrants Made It Happen
|last1=Kennedy
|first1=Lesley
|date=May 10, 2019
|publisher=A&E Television Networks, LLC.
|access-date=2021-03-18
|archive-date=2021-05-26
|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210526135325/https://www.history.com/news/transcontinental-railroad-chinese-immigrants
|dead-url=no
}}</ref>。这些工作完毕之后，很多[[华工|华工]]便寻找其他职业，如洗衣工或工厂员工
<ref name=Hittell>{{cite book
|url=https://archive.org/details/gb0e4-lf4RejkC
|title=History of California
|last1=Hittell
|first1=Theodore H.
|volume=IV
|publisher=N.J. Stone & Company
|date=1898
|location=San Francisco
|chapter=III {{!}} Early State Administrations: Bigler
|pages=89–113
|chapter-url=https://archive.org/details/gb0e4-lf4RejkC/page/n83/mode/1up
}}</ref>{{rp|99–100}}。华工在美国受到相当大的偏见，很多白人认为华人的低价勞力会压低他们自己的工资
<ref name=Cross>{{cite book
|url=https://archive.org/details/historyoflabormo00cros
|first=Ira
|last=Cross
|chapter=VII: 'The Chinese Must Go'
|date=1935
|title=A History of the Labor Movement in California
|publisher=University of California Press
|location=Berkeley, California
|pages=88–129
|chapter-url=https://archive.org/details/historyoflabormo00cros/page/88/mode/2up
}}</ref>{{rp|88}}。

从1873年开始， 美国进入一个长期的[[w:Long_Depression|经济衰退]]，1877年[[加利福尼亚州|加州]]的矿业也告失败，以至三藩市的失业率高达20%。美国工人对“中国佬”的偏见也更加高，[[美国反中情绪|美国反中情绪]]也越激烈
<ref name=Boomtown-1>{{cite news
|url=https://www.kqed.org/news/10413670/draft-boomtown-history-2a
|title=Boomtown，1870s: Decade of Bonanza，Bust and Unbridled Racism
|last1=Brekke
|first1=Dan
|date=February 11, 2015
|work=KQED
|accessdate=2021-03-18
|archive-date=2021-05-02
|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210502174528/https://www.kqed.org/news/10413670/draft-boomtown-history-2a
|dead-url=no
}}</ref>。

==沙场集会==
1877年7月23日美国一个新生的[[工会|工会]]'''美国工人工会'''（'''[[w:Workingmen's_Party_of_the_United_States|Workingmen's Party of the United States]]'''）在[[旧金山市政厅|旧金山市政厅]]旁的沙场组织了大型集会，为支持东岸[[w:Pittsburgh_railroad_strike_of_1877|铁路工人罢工]]
<ref name=Boomtown-2>{{cite news
|url=https://www.kqed.org/news/10429550/boomtown-history-2b
|title=Boomtown，1870s: 'The Chinese Must Go!'
|last1=Brekke
|first1=Dan
|date=February 12, 2015
|work=KQED
|accessdate=2021-03-18
|archive-date=2021-03-17
|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210317031318/https://www.kqed.org/news/10429550/boomtown-history-2b
|dead-url=no
}}</ref>。

参与这集会的人数达8,000，包括一些"反苦力会" (Anti Coolie club) 会员。虽然演说者都没有提起中国人，但群众内很多人在大喊反华口号
<ref>{{cite news
|url=https://cdnc.ucr.edu/?a=d&d=DAC18770723.2.17
|title=The Great Strike. A Day of Terror at Pittsburg.
|date=July 23, 1877
|newspaper=Daily Alta California
|publisher=California Digital Newspaper Collection
|volume=29
|issue=9967
}}</ref>。演讲时有一位中国人正好于集会旁边经过，他被打后，群众便大声喊叫：“去唐人街” (On to Chinatown)
<ref name=Perlman>{{cite book
|url=https://archive.org/details/historylabourin00brangoog
|first=Selig
|last=Perlman
|chapter=The Anti-Chinese Agitation in California
|editor1=Commons，John R.
|title=History of Labour in the United States
|location=New York
|publisher=Macmillan
|year=1921
|volume=2
|pages=252–268
|chapter-url=https://archive.org/details/historylabourin00brangoog/page/n275/mode/2up
}}</ref>{{rp|253}}。
